HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 36
BY REPRESENTATIVE EGAN
COMMENDATIONS: Commends James C. Walsh on being named 2026 Hibernian of the
Year in Louisiana
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend James C. Walsh on being named 2026 Hibernian of the Year in Louisiana.
3 WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize James C. Walsh for many achievements
4 and to commend him for being recognized by the Ancient Order of Hibernians of Louisiana
5 as the 2026 Hibernian of the Year; and
6 WHEREAS, Mr. Walsh was born in 1940 in New Brunswick, New Jersey, to an
7 immigrant family; his father, James Patrick Walsh, immigrated from Charlestown, County
8 Mayo, Ireland, to the United States in the 1920s; his mother Elizabeth's family arrived from
9 Hungary and Czechoslovakia in the 1890s; and
10 WHEREAS, Mr. Walsh's first language was Hungarian, which he learned from his
11 beloved grandmother, Erzebet "Elsie" Nagy; and
12 WHEREAS, Mr. Walsh worked at automotive parts factories while taking night
13 classes at Rutgers University; he enrolled at the University of Alabama, where he met his
14 lifelong friend, client, and business partner, future NFL Hall of Fame quarterback Joe
15 Namath; he also befriended future New Orleans civic leader Eddie Sapir; and
16 WHEREAS, after completing his undergraduate degree, Mr. Walsh remained in
17 Tuscaloosa, Alabama, to attend the University of Alabama School of Law; he graduated in
18 1966 and began his legal career in New York City; and
19 WHEREAS, Mr. Walsh initially practiced civil defense in Brooklyn, but soon after,
20 he began negotiating contracts and endorsements for Namath; he proved to be an innovator
21 in sports and entertainment law by securing endorsements and ventures ranging from
