1 typewriters and razors to television appearances; he famously spearheaded Namath's deal
2 to promote BeautyMist pantyhose; and
3 WHEREAS, Mr. Walsh co-founded a law firm with Johnny Carson's attorney and
4 manager, Henry Bushkin, and film producer and financier, Arnold Kopelson; he grew his
5 client roster to include other prominent athletes, including NFL quarterback Doug Williams
6 and boxer Sean O'Grady; and
7 WHEREAS, Mr. Walsh discovered comedian Andy Kaufman in New York in the
8 1970s; he served as the comedian's first agent and manager and secured performance slots
9 at prominent clubs in New York City; and
10 WHEREAS, Mr. Walsh met local fashion maven, Yvonne LaFleur, in 1979 during
11 a flight from New Orleans to New York; he sparked a romance with her six months later
12 while visiting Lucky Pierre's in New Orleans, and they married in 1981; and
13 WHEREAS, Mr. Walsh relocated to New Orleans after marrying Yvonne, and they
14 raised seven children together; he resides in the city today; and
15 WHEREAS, Mr. Walsh won an Emmy for his role as an executive producer of the
16 HBO Sports documentary, Namath; he is a longtime member of the founding board of the
17 Joe Namath Charitable Foundation; and
18 WHEREAS, James C. Walsh's life is defined by his faith, loyalty, friendship, and
19 distinctly Irish ability to turn hard work and imagination into an inspiring story; he is most
20 deserving of the highest recognition for his incredible achievements.
21 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
22 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend James C. Walsh on being named 2026
23 Hibernian of the Year in Louisiana and does hereby extend sincere wishes that he remain
24 prosperous in all of his endeavors.
